@Generated(value="com.guidewire.pl.metadata.codegen.Codegen", comments="UserSearchCriteria.eti;UserSearchCriteria.eix;UserSearchCriteria.etx") public class UserSearchCriteria extends com.guidewire.pl.persistence.code.BeanBase implements Versionable, Serializable
UserSearchCriteria Encapsulates the search criteria for a User search. Key points in the system for user search include, the user search from the admin page, user picker on assignment pages, and the general user search page.

    • getPublicID

      public String getPublicID()
      The external ID for this entity.

      PublicID values are automatically created during the commit, if not previously set. The format is random, meeting security requirements based on current industry standards. For example:

      • pc:SYinDB2XTOgNZFs1NpxU8
      • pc:Sf8QS4N5RBS-h8_pj-Oy_
      • pc:SBwBzylneecSNr6_Ub4IO
      Your configuration code must not assume any particular format for PublicID values, in either the prefix or body portion of the string, or even assume the existence of a prefix. Do not make any assumptions at all about the content of a PublicID value, including expectations that values are sequential, numeric, or prefixed.

      You can subclass and override AbstractBundleTransactionCallback.afterSetIds(gw.pl.persistence.core.Bundle) if you need to see the value in the same commit. 

      
  var note = new Note(bundle)
  bundle.addBundleTransactionCallback(new AbstractBundleTransactionCallback() {
     override function afterSetIds(b : Bundle) {
       log.info("Created Note " + note.PublicID)
     }
  })
      Specified by:
      getPublicID in interface KeyableBean
      Specified by:
      getPublicID in interface Versionable
      Returns:
      the external id.

    • performGroupUserSearch

      public IQueryBeanResult performGroupUserSearch()
      Searches for visible UserGroups with users matching the last name and first name fields specified in the criteria. Visible user groups have groups that are in the same security zone(s) as the current user (see
      invalid reference 
      entity.User#getGroupsInSecurityZones()
      ) unless the user has the special "view all users" permission, in which case all groups are visible.

      Note that since this search takes its results from the UserGroup table, users with no groups will not be returned.

      Returns:
      all visible user groups that match the criteria
